Maintenance policy
==================

This package is maintained as a ZFS-friendly XanMod kernel sources package,
not as an automatic mirror of every latest XanMod release.

For ZFS users, the maintainer intends to keep at least one installable
xanmod-sources ebuild that is compatible with the Linux version supported by
the stable sys-fs/zfs or sys-fs/zfs-kmod packages in the Gentoo main tree.
Newer XanMod series may also be packaged, but they are only considered
ZFS-friendly when the corresponding ZFS module package declares support for
that Linux series.

The zfs USE flag is a compatibility gate. When enabled, it adds dependencies
on ZFS module packages that are known to support the kernel series used by the
selected ebuild. This is meant to make Portage report an unsupported ZFS/kernel
combination during dependency resolution instead of letting users discover the
problem later while building the ZFS module.

Old ebuilds are dropped cautiously. Third-party kernels are often used on
systems where ZFS module availability matters, and removing the last ebuild
compatible with a stable ZFS module can force users into unwanted keyword
changes or kernel downgrades.

Users should accept keywords with an explicit kernel-series bound instead of
unconditionally accepting every future version of this package. Patchlevel
updates within the same Linux series are normally expected to be safe, while
major or minor series jumps should be reviewed against ZFS module support
first. For example, to use the 6.19 line:

  <sys-kernel/xanmod-sources-6.20 ~amd64

When deliberately moving to a newer kernel line, update the bound only after
confirming that the matching sys-fs/zfs or sys-fs/zfs-kmod version supports
that Linux series. For example:

  <sys-kernel/xanmod-sources-7.1 ~amd64
